On December 29, the second lion was also killed. Both lions differed from the others in that they did not have a mane, although they were males. The length of both lions from the tip of the nose to the tip of the tail was about nine feet (three meters). In 1907, Patterson's book Cannibals was published. from Tsavo ”(The Man-eaters of Tsavo; Russian translation of individual chapters was published in the almanac“ On land and at sea ”, 1962). In 1924, Patterson sold the skins of lions to the Field Museum of Natural History in Chicago.